WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.500
Water moves continuously through the water cycle.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.500
It evaporates from oceans and lakes, turning into vapor.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.500
This vapor rises and condenses to form clouds.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:24.500
When clouds become heavy, water falls as rain or snow.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.500
The water then flows back into rivers and oceans.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:36.000
This cycle repeats forever.